('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'A Pre-Qualified WPS in AWS D1.1 requires:', 'PQR testing', 'Compliance with all provisions of §5 (Prequalification)', 'Owner-only approval', 'No documentation', 'B', 'A prequalified WPS does not require PQR testing but must comply with every provision of D1.1 §5 — base metal, joint detail, electrode, and parameters.', 'AWS D1.1 §5', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'In AWS D1.1, qualification of a welder on a 1G groove qualifies the welder for:', 'Flat groove only', 'Flat groove and flat fillet', 'All positions', 'Vertical groove', 'B', '1G qualification covers flat groove and flat fillet welding only — vertical and overhead require additional position qualification.', 'AWS D1.1 §6.21', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'A WPS qualified by PQR is qualified within what range of base metal thickness?', 'Exactly the test thickness', 'The thickness range allowed by §6 essential variables', 'Any thickness', 'Within ±10%', 'B', 'PQR test thickness establishes a qualified range per the essential variables tables in §6.', 'AWS D1.1 §6', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'When inspecting a multi-pass weld, the inspector should:', 'Inspect only the final pass', 'Inspect each pass between deposition', 'Only the root and cap', 'Only when called', 'B', 'Multi-pass weld inspection requires monitoring of fit-up, root, intermediate passes, and final pass to catch issues early.', 'AWS B5.1', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Carbon equivalent (CE) per AWS D1.1 is calculated as:', 'C + Mn/6', 'C + (Mn+Si)/6 + (Cr+Mo+V)/5 + (Ni+Cu)/15', 'C only', 'Mn × Si', 'B', 'AWS D1.1 Annex H provides this CE formula for estimating hardenability and preheat requirements.', 'AWS D1.1 Annex H', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Hydrogen-induced cracking (HIC) requires three conditions:', 'Heat, time, oxygen', 'Hydrogen, susceptible microstructure, tensile stress', 'Cold, dry, dirty', 'High amps, low travel, AC', 'B', 'HIC requires (1) diffusible hydrogen, (2) a crack-susceptible microstructure (typically martensite), and (3) sufficient tensile stress.', 'AWS D1.1', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Postweld heat treatment (PWHT) is performed to:', 'Cool the weld faster', 'Relieve residual stress and temper hard microstructures', 'Increase weld hardness', 'Add carbon', 'B', 'PWHT relieves residual welding stresses and tempers martensitic regions of the HAZ to improve toughness.', 'ASME IX', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'ndt', 'For RT inspection of a 1 inch thick weld using gamma rays, the recommended source is:', 'Iridium-192', 'Cobalt-60', 'X-ray only', 'Selenium-75', 'A', 'Iridium-192 is suitable for steel thicknesses approximately 0.5 to 2.5 inches. Cobalt-60 is used for thicker sections.', 'ASME V', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'ndt', 'In UT shear wave inspection, the angle beam is most often:', '45°', '60°', '70°', '45°, 60°, or 70° depending on geometry', 'D', 'Angle beam shear wave inspection uses 45°, 60°, or 70° transducers chosen based on weld geometry and code requirements.', 'AWS D1.1 §8', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'ndt', 'Liquid penetrant testing (PT) is used on:', 'Ferromagnetic materials only', 'Non-porous materials regardless of magnetism', 'Only stainless steel', 'Only aluminum', 'B', 'PT works on any non-porous material and is commonly used on austenitic stainless and aluminum where MT is ineffective.', 'AWS B5.16', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'AWS D1.1 §8 covers:', 'WPS qualification', 'Stud welding', 'Statically loaded structures', 'Cyclically loaded structures', 'C', 'AWS D1.1 §8 contains specific provisions for statically loaded structures, including acceptance criteria.', 'AWS D1.1 §8', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'For cyclically loaded structures, AWS D1.1 §9 has stricter requirements for:', 'Aesthetic appearance', 'Fatigue-related defects like undercut and reinforcement', 'Filler metal cost', 'Production speed', 'B', '§9 imposes tighter limits because cyclic loading drives fatigue cracking from any stress concentration.', 'AWS D1.1 §9', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'A weld with arc strikes outside the weld zone is:', 'Always acceptable', 'Generally rejectable per AWS D1.1 §7.30', 'Only rejected on stainless', 'Acceptable if ground smooth', 'B', 'AWS D1.1 §7.30 prohibits arc strikes on base metal — they create localized hardened zones and stress concentrations.', 'AWS D1.1 §7.30', 'medium'),
