('CWI', 'weld_symbols', 'A double V groove symbol indicates a groove weld:', 'On one side only', 'On both sides of the joint', 'In two passes', 'With backing', 'B', 'A double V symbol (Vs above and below the reference line) indicates groove preparation on both sides of the joint.', 'AWS A2.4', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Sensitization in austenitic stainless steels occurs when:', 'Heated below 800°F', 'Held in the 800-1500°F range causing chromium carbide precipitation', 'Welded with argon', 'Cold worked', 'B', 'Austenitic stainless held in 800-1500°F precipitates chromium carbides at grain boundaries, depleting Cr and reducing corrosion resistance.', 'AWS D1.6', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'To prevent sensitization in stainless welds, you should:', 'Use high carbon filler', 'Use low-carbon (L grade) filler and limit heat input', 'Preheat to 800°F', 'Slow cooling rates', 'B', 'L-grade fillers (304L, 316L) limit carbon to <0.03% to prevent carbide precipitation. Limiting heat input also helps.', 'AWS D1.6', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'A CWI''s primary responsibility is to:', 'Welder training', 'Verify welds and procedures meet code requirements', 'Set production schedules', 'Purchase materials', 'B', 'The CWI verifies code compliance — both the welding procedures and the resulting welds.', 'AWS QC1', 'easy'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'CWI certification is administered by:', 'OSHA', 'AWS', 'ASNT', 'API', 'B', 'AWS QC1 governs the CWI certification program administered by the American Welding Society.', 'AWS QC1', 'easy'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'CWI re-certification requires:', 'Nothing', 'Renewal every 3 years and recertification every 9 years', 'Annual testing', 'New testing every year', 'B', 'AWS QC1 requires CWI renewal every 3 years and full recertification (or eye exam + experience) every 9 years.', 'AWS QC1', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'In visual inspection, the inspector should have visual acuity of:', '20/20 with correction', 'At least Snellen 20/40 with or without correction (Jaeger J2 near vision)', '20/100', 'No requirement', 'B', 'AWS QC1 requires near vision capability of Jaeger J2 or equivalent at 12 inches, with or without correction.', 'AWS QC1', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'For acceptable fillet weld quality, the convexity should not exceed:', '0.07W + 0.06 in', '0.07W + 0.06 in (where W is the actual face width)', '1/4 in', 'No limit', 'B', 'AWS D1.1 §5.24 limits fillet weld convexity to 0.07W + 0.06 in (in inches), where W is the actual face width.', 'AWS D1.1 §5.24', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'AWS D1.5 governs welding of:', 'Buildings', 'Bridges', 'Pressure vessels', 'Pipelines', 'B', 'AWS D1.5 is the Bridge Welding Code, jointly published with AASHTO for highway and railway bridge structures.', 'AWS D1.5', 'easy'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Cold cracking in HSLA steels typically occurs at temperatures:', 'Above 800°F', 'Below 400°F', 'During welding only', 'Only above 1000°F', 'B', 'Cold (delayed/hydrogen) cracking occurs as the weld cools below approximately 400°F, often hours after welding.', 'AWS D1.1', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'ndt', 'The minimum image quality indicator (IQI) sensitivity for RT per AWS D1.1 is:', '1-1T', '2-2T', '2-1T', '4-2T', 'C', 'AWS D1.1 §8.17 specifies the IQI penetrameter and essential hole based on material thickness, with 2-1T being a common requirement.', 'AWS D1.1 §8.17', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'When inspecting fit-up before welding, root opening tolerance per pre-qualified joints is:', 'No tolerance allowed', '±1/16 in for most joints', '±1/4 in always', 'Welder''s discretion', 'B', 'Per AWS D1.1 §5.22, fit-up tolerances on prequalified joints are typically ±1/16 in on root opening.', 'AWS D1.1 §5.22', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'AWS B5.1 provides the standard for:', 'Filler metals', 'Qualification of welding inspectors', 'Welding procedures', 'Base metals', 'B', 'AWS B5.1 specifies qualification requirements for welding inspectors, complementary to QC1.', 'AWS B5.1', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Interpass temperature should be:', 'Higher than preheat', 'Maintained between minimum preheat and the maximum specified by the WPS', 'As low as possible', 'Not measured', 'B', 'Interpass temperature must be at or above preheat minimum and at or below the WPS maximum to control mechanical properties.', 'AWS D1.1', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'Weld profile gages are used to measure:', 'Hardness', 'Fillet weld leg, throat, and convexity', 'Travel speed', 'Voltage', 'B', 'Fillet weld gages physically measure leg length, theoretical throat, and convexity against acceptance criteria.', 'AWS D1.1', 'easy'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Hot cracking is most associated with:', 'Hydrogen', 'Solidification of high-restraint, narrow welds with sulfur/phosphorus contamination', 'Cold base metal', 'Excessive preheat', 'B', 'Hot (solidification) cracking occurs at high temperatures during freezing, driven by impurities and restraint.', 'AWS D1.1', 'medium'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'In AWS D1.1, the term "essential variable" refers to:', 'Any setting on the machine', 'A variable that, if changed beyond limits, requires WPS requalification', 'Travel speed only', 'Color of arc', 'B', 'Essential variables (per §6 tables) are parameters that affect weld properties enough that changes require requalification.', 'AWS D1.1 §6', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'ndt', 'PT (penetrant testing) cannot detect:', 'Surface cracks', 'Subsurface defects', 'Surface porosity', 'Open laps', 'B', 'PT relies on capillary action drawing penetrant into surface-breaking discontinuities — it cannot detect subsurface defects.', 'AWS B5.16', 'easy'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'A weld inspector should reference what document for visual acceptance criteria?', 'OSHA standards', 'The applicable code (e.g., AWS D1.1 Table 6.1) and contract specifications', 'Welder discretion', 'Customer feedback', 'B', 'The governing welding code plus any project-specific contract specifications define visual acceptance criteria.', 'AWS B5.1', 'easy'),
('CWI', 'codes_standards', 'A WPS for fillet welds only must qualify what type of test?', 'Bend tests on a groove', 'Fillet weld break test or macroetch', 'No testing', 'Tensile only', 'B', 'AWS D1.1 §6.13 allows fillet-weld-only WPS qualification via fillet break test plus macroetch examination.', 'AWS D1.1 §6.13', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'metallurgy', 'Peening of intermediate weld passes is:', 'Required by AWS D1.1', 'Permitted to control distortion but not on root or final passes', 'Always prohibited', 'Used to add carbon', 'B', 'AWS D1.1 §7.27 permits peening to control residual stress and distortion on intermediate passes only — never on root or cap.', 'AWS D1.1 §7.27', 'hard'),
('CWI', 'visual_inspection', 'When inspecting a butt weld, the inspector verifies:', 'Cosmetics only', 'Fit-up, root condition, fusion, profile, and final dimensions against code', 'Cost only', 'Time spent', 'B', 'Comprehensive butt weld inspection covers all stages from fit-up through final visual against the applicable code.', 'AWS D1.1 §6', 'easy');
